Running Python code interactively: # Complete implementation with proper pagination and error handling
import requests

# Get OAuth token
auth_response = requests.post(
    "http://the-agent-company.com:8929/oauth/token",
    data={
        "grant_type": "password",
        "username": "root",
        "password": "theagentcompany"
    }
)
auth_response.raise_for_status()
access_token = auth_response.json()["access_token"]
headers = {"Authorization": f"Bearer {access_token}"}

# Get all projects with pagination
projects = []
page = 1
while True:
    response = requests.get(
        "http://the-agent-company.com:8929/api/v4/projects",
        headers=headers,
        params={"page": page, "per_page": 100}
    )
    response.raise_for_status()
    
    if not response.json():
        break
        
    projects.extend(response.json())
    page += 1

# Remove members from each project
for project in projects:
    # Get project members
    members = []
    page = 1
    while True:
        response = requests.get(
            f"http://the-agent-company.com:8929/api/v4/projects/{project['id']}/members",
            headers=headers,
            params={"page": page, "per_page": 100}
        )
        response.raise_for_status()
        
        if not response.json():
            break
            
        members.extend(response.json())
        page += 1

    # Delete each member
    for member in members:
        response = requests.delete(
            f"http://the-agent-company.com:8929/api/v4/projects/{project['id']}/members/{member['id']}",
            headers=headers
        )
        response.raise_for_status()

print(f"Removed {len(members)} members from project {project['id']}")
